cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.LG

This paper discusses decentralized cryptocurrency protocols, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Proof of Stake mechanisms also suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The analysis of existing protocols and the presentation of novel protocols involve mathematical modeling and algorithm design, which are relevant to the subfields of graph theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
